feat(llm): add Groq model fallback chain with retry + parse-failure fallthrough

Default chain: openai/gpt-oss-120b -> openai/gpt-oss-20b ->
openai/gpt-oss-safeguard-20b -> llama-3.3-70b-versatile.

- chat() now runs the chain; each model retries up to 2x with exponential
  backoff on transient transport errors only, and skips immediately on
  non-retryable errors or validator (JSON/Zod) failures
- extract.ts and enrich.ts pass JSON+Zod validation as a `validate`
  callback so a model returning malformed JSON triggers fallback rather
  than a hard ingest failure
- summarize.ts and qa.ts use the same chain transparently for plain text
- Optional GROQ_MODEL pins a single model (no fallback) for debugging;
  GROQ_MODELS overrides the chain via comma-separated list
- Add scripts/smoke-llm.ts for ad-hoc verification of the chain
